This PR adds a new utility function to simplify calling functions in a specific injection context.

Similar to the JS native [Function.prototype.bind()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Function/bind), the goal is to simplify calling a function. By binding the target function to an injection context, the caller no longer needs to pass service instances or other resolved injection tokens as parameters. The caller also doesn't have to use `runInInjectionContext` every time when they call the target function anymore.

We have successfully used this utility function for the past 8 months in a semi-large project without any issues, so I thought this might be a good addition for the whole community.

