### Description

`resource` and `rxResource` expect a signal for the `request`. 

```typescript
export interface Post {
  id?: number;
  title: string;
  body: string;
}

@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root',
})
export class PostsService {
  private readonly httpClient = inject(HttpClient);

  public post = signal(null);
  public createPost= (): ResourceRef<Post> =>
    rxResource({
      request: () => this.post(),
      loader: ({ request }) => {
        if (!request) return of(null);
        return this.httpClient.post<Post>(
          'https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts',
          request
        );
      },
    });
}
```

The example above (based on most public examples) demonstrates how this pattern requires the `post` signal to exist outside of the `createPost` function. The service now lacks cohesion since other potential methods/functions are unlikely to utilize the `post` signal. E.g., `getAllPosts()`.

One workaround is to change the createPost signature to accept a signal parameter:

```typescript
public createPost = (post: Signal<Post>) => rxResource({ request: () => post, ... })
```

Unfortunately, this just moves the cohesion problem to the service consumer.

### Proposed solution

I believe `request` should be exposed as a `WriteableSignal`:

```typescript
// service
 ...
  public createPost = (): ResourceRef<Post> =>
    rxResource({
      loader: ({ request }) => {
        return this.httpClient.post<Post>(
          'https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts',
          request
        );
      },
    });
 ...

// component
...
private readonly postsService = inject(PostsService);
public createPostResource = this.postsService.createPost();

public createPost(post: Post): void {
   this.createPostResource.request.set(post);
}
```

This would improve cohesion in services utilizing `rxResource`.

### Alternatives considered

As a personal workaround, I extended `ResourceRef` with a `data: WriteableSignal` property. `data` isn't the best name, but `request` was taken :)

```typescript
export interface DataResourceRef<T = unknown, U = unknown>
  extends ResourceRef<T> {
  data: WritableSignal<U>;
}

export interface Post { ... }

@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root',
})
export class PostsService {
  private readonly httpClient = inject(HttpClient);

  public createPost = (post: Post): DataResourceRef<Post, Post> => {
    const data = signal<Post>(post);
    return {
      data,
      ...rxResource({
        request: () => data(),
        loader: ({ request }) => {
          if (!request) return of(null);
          return this.httpClient.post<Post>(
            'https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/posts',
            request
          );
        },
      }),
    };
  };
```

```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  imports: [FormsModule, ReactiveFormsModule, JsonPipe],
  templateUrl: './app.component.html'
})
export class App {
  private readonly postsService = inject(PostsService);
  protected createPostResource = this.postsService.createPost(null);
  protected form = new FormGroup({
    title: new FormControl(''),
    body: new FormControl(''),
  });

  addPost(): void {
    this.createPostResource.data.set(this.form.getRawValue());
  }
}
```

